The Bucharest Exchange Trading index (BET or BET-10) was the first index developed by Bucharest Stock Exchange. It is the reference index for the capital markets. BET follows the evolution of 10 most liquid companies listed on BVB regulated market, excluding financial investment companies (SIFs). It is an index weighted by free float capitalization. The maximum weight of the symbol is 20%. The main selection criterion is companyâ€™s liquidity. Starting with 2015, additional requirements of transparency, quality reporting and communication with investors will be imposed.
